jobs_results.title: Ios developer - full remote
jobs_results.description:
Desde GeeksHubs estamos trabajando con una importante empresa del sector telecomunicaciones.

Buscamos un/a iOS DEVELOPER con al menos 3 años de experiencia de desarrollo de aplicaciones en entornos Swift para unirse a su equipo.

Tus funciones principales:
> Responsabilidad principal en la codificación, entrega y actualización de las aplicaciones móviles desarrolladas internamente por la empresa.
> Diseñar e implementar nuevas funcionalidades de cara al usuario en las grandes y complejas aplicaciones móviles de la empresa. Trabajarás en estrecha colaboración con los equipos de producto y diseño para personalizar la experiencia de las aplicaciones para la plataforma iOS.
> Responsabilidad de principio a fin para las aplicaciones internas desde la codificación hasta el despliegue, incluyendo la portabilidad, el cumplimiento de las especificaciones, el diseño técnico, la creación del plan de pruebas, el apoyo al despliegue, la revisión del código.

¿Qué hace falta para formar parte de la banda?
Formación de Ingeniería informática, Ingeniería de Telecomunicaciones o similar.
> +3 años de experiencia codificando aplicaciones iOS sintiéndose cómodo con Swift y tener un amplio conocimiento de los patrones modernos de diseño de software móvil (MVVM, MVP, TCA, etc).
> Experiencia aprovechando paradigmas/herramientas modernas de iOS (Xcode, herramientas de rendimiento, herramientas de construcción, técnicas de optimización y frameworks internos).
> Interés y/o experiencia con SwiftUI.
> Experiencia con programación multithreading.
> Experiencia escribiendo código simple y limpio, pruebas unitarias y más importante código comprobable.
> Capacidad para identificar las características únicas de las capacidades de dispositivos específicos y definir la interfaz de usuario adecuada y los requisitos del producto en consecuencia.
> Capacidad de liderazgo y excelentes dotes de comunicación e interpersonales con capacidad para trabajar con una amplia variedad de departamentos. Trabajamos en un entorno ágil, donde la colaboración está en el centro de todo lo que hacemos.
> Capacidad para contribuir a la priorización de características con un fuerte sentido del diseño orientado al usuario.
> Capacidad para trabajar de forma independiente, establecer plazos y ejecutar el plan.
> Interés y capacidad para aprender otros lenguajes de programación según sea necesario.
> Gran capacidad analítica y de resolución de problemas.
> Nivel de inglés B2 (imprescindible para poder participar en reuniones técnicas).

jobs_results.title: Junior iOS Engineer (They/She/He)
jobs_results.description:
Not your usual app. We are the fastest-growing multi-category app connecting millions of users with businesses, and couriers, offering on-demand services from more than 170,000 local restaurants, grocers and supermarkets, and high street retail stores.

We operate in more than 1500 cities across 25 countries. Every year, +200k merchants generate over 4B€ in sales through our platform and over 20M customers get their goods delivered in minutes.

We have a vision: To give everyone easy access to anything in their cities.

And this is where your ride starts…

YOUR MISSION

We are hiring for multiple teams at Glovo, with diverse scopes, User Acquisition Flow, Ordering, Checkout, payments, etc. We are looking for someone eager to learn and grow their professional career on mobile.

THE JOURNEY
• Be a part of a cross-functional team working closely with backend and frontend engineers
• Develop software using modern engineering approaches and agile principles
• Make our technology and our team scale as the business grows
• Own your deliverables from start to finish
• Deliver high-quality solutions
• Participate in the team’s life and contribute to decision-making

What You Will Bring To The Ride
• Computer Science or similar degree
• Knowledge of Swift and iOS SDK
• Knowledge of object-oriented programming and software architecture
• Ability to write good unit tests is a must
• Analytical and problem-solving skills
• Vivid interest in at least one area outside of coding (architecture, algorithms, optimization, automation, scalability, etc.)
• Fluid communication in English
• [Bonus-points] Understanding of reactive programming (ReactiveKit, ReactiveCocoa, UIKit etc)
• [Bonus-points] Understanding of AutoLayout and ability to create UI from code
• [Nice-to-have] Experience with Full stack technologies (Java/Kotlin)
• [Nice-to-have] Participation in open source projects
• [Nice-to-have] Basic knowledge of DataDog, Crash reporting on iOS

Even if it seems you don't meet our musts don't let it stop you, we are all about finding the best talent out there! Skills can be learned, and embracing diversity is invaluable.

We Believe Driven Talent Deserves
• 🌟 An enticing equity plan *if applicable
• 💪 Top-notch private health insurance to keep you at your peak.
• 🍔 Monthly Glovo credit to satisfy your cravings!
• 💳 Discounts on transportation, food, and even kindergarten expenses or office-based nursery.
• 🏊 Discounted gym memberships to keep you energized.
• 🏖️ The freedom to work from home two days a week, and the opportunity to work from anywhere for up to three weeks a year. .
• 👪 Enhanced parental leave (*if applicable)
• 🧠 Online therapy and wellbeing benefits

We’ll deliver a non-vanilla culture built on talent, where we work to amplify the impact on millions of people, paving the way forward together.

At Glovo, we truly value diversity for the positive impact it brings to our teams, products, and culture. We're dedicated to providing equal opportunities for talent from all backgrounds.

Feel free to note your pronouns in your application (e.g., she/her/hers, he/him/his, they/them/theirs, etc).

Delve into our culture by taking a peek at our Instagram and check out our Linkedin and website!

jobs_results.title: iOS Developer for SDK | (NLN68)
jobs_results.description:
Smadex is a cutting-edge ad-tech company: we process more than 2.5 million ad requests per second, replying under 100ms. Every day we generate several TBs of data that need to be processed, analyzed, and aggregated, so our real-time components get smarter every day. We need you to help us keep our platform in motion, so if you like challenges and enjoy owning your code from design to production, this is meant for you. Keep reading!

This position is based in Barcelona.
Role Overview

We are looking for an iOS Engineer who will be at the forefront of building our Ads SDK. In this role, you will enable publishers (app developers) to effectively optimize and monetize their iOS apps through advanced advertising solutions.
The Opportunity:
• Design and develop an iOS Ads SDK.
• Keep the SDK current with the latest iOS advancements as well as new technologies and industry trends across leading app platforms.
• Provide integration support for customers and maintain detailed, user-friendly SDK documentation.
• Work closely with cross-functional teams across our tech team to ensure the SDK seamlessly integrates with the Smadex platform.
Requirements and Qualifications:
• 3+ years of experience as a Software Engineer.
• Significant experience with iOS development with Swift and Objective-C.
• In-depth knowledge of multithreading, networking, and the internals of iOS, including optimization for performance and power efficiency.
• A strong passion for mobile platforms and a commitment to staying current with the latest iOS advancements.
Bonus Points:
• Experience building and distributing CocoaPods or Swift Packages.
• Knowledge of mobile advertising technologies such as MRAID and VAST.
• Experience building and distributing React Native and/or Unity plugins for iOS.

Please note that we do NOT provide VISA sponsorship. Candidates without a legal permit to work in Spain won't be considered.
What Will You Do at Smadex?
• Be the go-to person for iOS development in the company.
• Be an advocate of our “You build it, you run it” philosophy: you will own your code from design to production; testing, deploying, and monitoring. You will learn from every step in the software development process.
• Participate in code reviews, contribute to technical and architectural decisions, collaborate in a fast-paced environment where every opinion counts.
If you become a member of our team, you will get the chance to:
• Have a real impact on one of the hottest ad-tech companies in Barcelona and Europe.
• Be part of an agile team with a strong focus on innovation and technology, to continue improving your knowledge in the field.
• Work in a multicultural, young & talented environment with people from more than 28 different nationalities!
• Enjoy benefits such as a monthly ticket restaurant allowance, flexible working hours, DIR gym membership, LinkedIn Learning, daily fresh fruits & snacks, TGIF’s monthly activities, team-building events, and work anniversary celebrations.
• And more!

If you want to know more about us visit our website, and for a sneak peek of the cool stuff we build, check this out!

jobs_results.description:
¿De qué va la empresa en la que trabajarás?

Somos una empresa de soluciones móviles corporativas, la cual desde hace 10 años viene centrado su misión en acelerar la digitalización tecnológica de la sociedad, desarrollamos tanto webs como apps híbridas.

En estos años nuestro equipo ha dado forma a más de 1000 proyectos para 150 clientes con presencia nacional e internacional.

¿En qué creemos?

Nos basamos en cuatro valores fundamentales:
• Innovación, ofreciendo soluciones innovadoras de una manera profesional y rentable con un valor diferencial: el conocimiento experto en toda la cadena de valor.
• Compromiso ya que llevamos como propios los objetivos de la organización y superamos cualquier obstáculo para lograrlos.
• Proactividad, proveyendo y realizando acciones para mejorar sus servicios y calidad.
• Trabajo en equipo, contando con un equipo motivado y multidisciplinar que trabaja en perfecta coordinación para lograr los objetivos comunes.

Para proyecto estable se requiere un perfil PROGRAMADOR/A IOS

¿Cuáles son los REQUISITOS clave para este puesto?
• Indispensable experiencia en: SwiftUI, Core Data.
• Arquitectura MVVM.
• Deseable: Objective C.

¿Qué podemos ofrecerte?
• Contrato indefinido.
• Modalidad de trabajo: Teletrabajo.
• Expectativas salariales: según la experiencia demostrada.

Si estás interesado/a, ¡mándanos tu cv!
